title: College roundup: Jefferson CC romps over Corning in men’s soccer
text:
A A 
WATERTOWN — Thomas Leech and Eric Gibbs each scored twice as Jefferson Community College rolled to a 9-2 men’s soccer nonconference victory over Corning CC on Monday at JCC. 
Brenden Jacobs, Abdul Sanderson and Scott Dalby each supplied a goal and an assist for Jefferson CC (6-6, 3-2). 
Peter Gerould and Caleb Johnson each scored for Corning CC (3-9, 1-5). 
WOMEN’S SOCCER 
JEFFERSON CC 2, CORNING CC 1 
The Cannoneers scored twice in the opening eight minutes to secure the nonconference win over the Red Barons. 
Casey Webb got JCC (2-7-1, 0-3-1) on the board three minutes in with an unassisted goal. Bryanna Gagnon followed that up five minutes later with an unassisted goal of her own. 
Corning (2-10, 0-6) stayed in the game behind a dozen saves from Taylor White. Rachael Sutryk scored for the Red Barons. 
WOMEN’S HOCKEY 
BOSTON COLLEGE 7, ST. LAWRENCE 3 
Alex Carpenter’s three goals and one assist paced Boston College to a victory over St. Lawrence University and a two-game sweep in Boston. 
Makenna Newkirk added a goal and two assist for the Eagles (4-0), ranked second in the country. 
Kailee Heidersbach, Kayla Nielsen and Kennedy Marchment each scored for the Saints (0-5-1). 
GOLF 
ROOS’ REID 6TH AT USCAA 
SUNY Canton junior Nolan Reid carded a 4-over par 76 to sit in a tie for sixth place out of the 115-golfer field on the first day at the USCAA Championships in State College, Pa. 
Reid’s outing helped the Roos into 5th place out of 18 teams after the opening round of play. Cleary University is in first after 18 holes of the 36-hole competition with 294. strokes.
